# Market Surveillance demo — copy to `.env` and edit, or just `docker compose up`.
# Every value has a sensible default; nothing here is required to see the demo run.

# ── Admin bootstrap (the provisioner registers this user on first boot) ───────
ADMIN_USER=desk
ADMIN_PASSWORD=Surveil1234!
ORG_NAME=Surveillance Desk

# ── Market-data generator ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RATE_PER_SEC=5
SPOOF_EVERY_SEC=20
SYMBOLS=ACME,GLOBEX,INITECH,HOOLI,VEHEMENT

# ── LLM provider (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Leave blank to let Pulse auto-detect a local model / fall back gracefully —
# the pipeline still runs end to end, the memo is just a placeholder.
# For a real, regulator-grade compliance memo set a cloud provider + key:
#   LLM_PROVIDER=anthropic   LLM_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5   LLM_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#   LLM_PROVIDER=openai      LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini         LLM_API_KEY=sk-...
LLM_PROVIDER=
LLM_MODEL=
LLM_API_KEY=

# ── MCP desk-alert credentials (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────
# The pipeline's Desk Alert (MCP) node pages Slack / PagerDuty / Jira. To enable
# REAL dispatch, install + configure those plugins in Pulse (Settings → MCP /
# Integrations) and paste the tokens there after first boot. Without them the
# pipeline still delivers every alert to the desk-intake console via the webhook
# sink — that is the screen you record.
